<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}-{8}{y}={51}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{3}{y}=-{51}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{3},-{9}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+-{8}{y}={51}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}={51}-{\left(-{8}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{51}-{\left(-{8}{y}\right)}}}{{7}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{\left(\frac{{{51}-{\left(-{8}{y}\right)}}}{{7}}\right)}+{3}{y}=-{51}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{8}}{{7}}\cdot{\left({51}\right)}-\frac{{8}}{{7}}{\left(-{8}\right)}{y}+{3}{y}=-{51}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{58.285714285714}-{\left({9.1428571428571}\right)}{y}+{3}{y}=-{51}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9.1428571428571}{y}+{\left({3}\right)}{y}=-{51}-{58.285714285714}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9.1428571428571}{y}+{\left({3}\right)}{y}=-{109.28571428571}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({9.1428571428571}+{\left({3}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{109.28571428571}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{12.142857142857}{y}=-{109.28571428571}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{109.28571428571}}{{12.142857142857}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{9}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+-{8}{\left(-{9}\right)}={51}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{\left({72}\right)}={51}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}={51}-{\left({72}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}=-{21}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{21}}{{7}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{3}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{3},-{9}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

